00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:32,120
because these people cannot possibly consume

471
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:33,440
that amount of money.

472
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:35,720
We're taking it away from investment.

473
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:38,720
So that would have to be, you know, truthful about it.

474
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:40,320
We're taking it away from investment.

475
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:43,080
So the real question is,

476
00:26:43,080 --> 00:26:46,680
is the government good in doing investments?

477
00:26:46,680 --> 00:26:49,120
And everybody knows that it's not true.

478
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,480
It's not true.

479
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:53,160
The government, if you give it 10 billion dollars,

480
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:56,000
it's going to be wasted to a very large extent.

481
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:58,800
And we all agree on that.

482
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:03,360
So we have to think of ways in which the incentives

483
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:07,760
are set up so that the private sector produces

484
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:11,640
what we want, the green growth that we all agree we want.

485
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:13,440
So we need to think of that.

486
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:14,880
And this is a serious issue.

487
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:16,360
I mean, it's not trivial.

488
00:27:16,360 --> 00:27:19,240
And we need to work on it.

