00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:50,880
that is Galbraith said back in the 50s,

501
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:53,400
is characterized by what?

502
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:56,320
Private splendor and public squalor.

503
00:27:56,320 --> 00:28:01,080
And we're arguably, because of status externalities

504
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:05,680
and positional goods, we've constructed a society

505
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:08,600
where we have excessive levels of private consumption

506
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:11,280
and we under invest in public goods

507
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:12,960
and in public infrastructure.

508
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:14,960
And I think I agree with Robert Frank

509
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:17,440
that most of, or many of the investments that now

510
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:21,640
are most important, the public sector has to be in the lead

511
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:24,600
on that and it has to be done at a global level.

512
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,880
And so what works, I think, is something

513
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:29,960
that looks more like social democracy

514
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:34,880
than like laissez-fieck fear of capitalism.

